Opposition to Submit Kan No-Confidence Motion

-- B y   T a k a s h i   H i r o k a w a
-- 
2011-06-01T07:47:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/opposition-to-submit-kan-no-confidence-motion.html
Japanese opposition parties agreed to
submit a no-confidence motion against Prime Minister  Naoto Kan 
today, which likely will be voted on tomorrow.  The heads of the  Liberal Democratic Party  and New Komeito
party agreed to submit the measure, New Komeito Secretary-
General Yoshihisa Inoue told reporters today in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takashi Hirokawa in Tokyo at 
 thirokawa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Brinsley at 
 jbrinsley@bloomberg.net  